"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDczMTg0Nzk1Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/167#issuecomment-731847957"},"message":"hash(`The cat is out of the bag`, 16):                                          \ndc404b9607f47b878c3c5a813ae9d6df","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1606079638,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDczMTg0ODEwNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/167#issuecomment-731848105"},"message":"Here's the code I use to generate default hashes, if there are any mistakes please let me know before doing 18 combinations:\n```\n#include \"/projects/prvhash/prvhash42.h\"\n#include \"/projects/prvhash/prvhash42s.h\"\n#include \u003cstdio.h\u003e\n\nvoid printHash( const char* const s, const uint8_t* const Hash,\n\tconst int HashLen )\n{\n\tprintf( \"hash(`%s`, %i): \", s, HashLen );\n\n\tif( HashLen \u003e 8 )\n\t{\n\t\tprintf( \"\\n\" );\n\t}\n\n\tint i;\n\n\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c HashLen; i++ )\n\t{\n\t\tprintf( \"%02x\", Hash[ i ]);\n\t}\n\n\tprintf( \"\\n\\n\" );\n}\n\nint main()\n{\n\tconst char str1[] = \"The cat is out of the bag\";\n\tconst int str1len = (int) strlen( str1 );\n\tconst char str2[] = \"Only a toilet bowl does not leak\";\n\tconst size_t str2len = strlen( str2 );\n\tconst char str3[] = \"Only a toilet bowl does not leal\";\n\tconst size_t str3len = strlen( str3 );\n\n\tuint8_t Hash32[ 4 ];\n\tuint8_t Hash64[ 8 ];\n\tuint8_t Hash256[ 32 ];\n\tuint8_t Hash256b[ 32 ];\n\tuint8_t Hash512[ 64 ];\n\n\tprvhash42( (uint8_t*) str1, str1len, Hash32, 4, 0, 0 );\n\tprintHash( str1, Hash32, 4 );\n\n\tprvhash42( (uint8_t*) str1, str1len, Hash64, 8, 0, 0 );\n\tprintHash( str1, Hash64, 8 );\n\n\tprvhash42s_oneshot( (uint8_t*) str1, str1len, Hash64, 8 );\n\tprintHash( str1, Hash64, 8 );\n\n\tprvhash42s_oneshot( (uint8_t*) str2, str2len, Hash256, 32 );\n\tprintHash( str2, Hash256, 32 );\n\n\tprvhash42s_oneshot( (uint8_t*) str3, str3len, Hash256b, 32 );\n\tprintHash( str3, Hash256b, 32 );\n\n\tprvhash42s_oneshot( (uint8_t*) str2, str2len, Hash512, 64 );\n\tprintHash( str2, Hash512, 64 );\n\n\tPRVHASH42S_CTX ctx;\n\tprvhash42s_init( \u0026ctx, Hash256, 32, 0, 0 );\n\tprvhash42s_update( \u0026ctx, (uint8_t*) str2, 14 );\n\tprvhash42s_update( \u0026ctx, (uint8_t*) str2 + 14, 15 );\n\tprvhash42s_update( \u0026ctx, (uint8_t*) str2 + 14 + 15, 3 );\n\tprvhash42s_final( \u0026ctx );\n\n\tprintHash( str2, Hash256, 32 );\n\n\tuint8_t Hash128[ 16 ];\n\tprvhash42s_oneshot( (uint8_t*) str1, str1len, Hash128, 16 );\n\tprintHash( str1, Hash128, 16 );\n}\n```","files":null},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1606417599,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50NDA0MzY1ODM1NQ=="},"status":2},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1606418893,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDczNDQ1MjU3NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/167#issuecomment-734452575"},"message":"@rurban Thank you for the update, except the speed benchmarks.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1606420211,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDczNDQ1ODIyNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/167#issuecomment-734458225"},"message":"By the way, I'm open to contact if PRVHASH causes program crashes or traps - I'll fix this.","files":null}]}